* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|en|/saɪˈliːʃə/}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|en|/saɪˈliʒə/}}

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}

# {{place|en|region|in central|cont/Europe}}, now chiefly in [[Poland]], with small portions in the [[Czech Republic]] and [[Germany]], from early modernity until 1945 predominantly German-speaking with [[Slavic]]-speaking minorities (and local majorities).

